This also eliminates the risk of an accidental shot that can occur in an automatic weapon with a closed bolt. In the first models of the Thompsons, the mechanism had a triangular trigger-lever mounted inside the bolt frame, which hit a striker with a striker made in the form of a separate part at the moment the bolt was brought groups to the extreme forward position. In the later model M1A1, the trigger was replaced with a striker fixed in the bolt cup. rear sight, the latter is a fixed with a V-shaped slot and an adjustable diopter sight that folds up.